16
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,510
Cách ước lượng và báo cáo về tiến độ dự án

17
00:00:49,510 --> 00:00:52,450
bao gồm việc quyết định thông tin dự án và dữ liệu nào

18
00:00:52,450 --> 00:00:55,730
 cần được thu thập, và những thông tin trên nên được

19
00:00:55,730 --> 00:00:58,170
 phân tích và báo cáo theo cách nào.

20
00:00:58,170 --> 00:01:00,110
những thông tin thu thập được thường sẽ

21
00:01:00,110 --> 00:01:02,870
dựa trên những thứ đã được chọn làm mục tiêu quan trọng

22
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:04,080
để đo lường.

23
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:07,700
Ví dụ, bạn sẽ ghi nhớ lượng thời gian dành cho các hoạt động,

24
00:01:07,700 --> 00:01:10,020
cách sử dụng các nguồn lực, các chi phí thực tế

25
00:01:10,020 --> 00:01:12,650
nhờ đó có thể đem so sánh với lượng thời gian, nguồn lực

26
00:01:12,650 --> 00:01:13,880
 và ngân quỹ đã dự tính trước.

27
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,930
There is often a focus on cost and schedule.

28
00:01:15,930 --> 00:01:17,770
And therefore, as a project manager,

29
00:01:17,770 --> 00:01:20,580
you may need answers to the following questions.

30
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:23,820
What is the current schedule and cost status for your project?

31
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:26,420
How much will it cost to complete the project?

32
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:29,040
And when will the project be completed?

33
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:32,370
If there are schedule slippages and/or cost overruns,

34
00:01:32,370 --> 00:01:35,090
what will be the forecast at completion?

35
00:01:35,090 --> 00:01:38,679
Are there potential problems that need to be addressed?

36
00:01:38,679 --> 00:01:40,470
The first step in answering those questions

37
00:01:40,470 --> 00:01:43,390
would be to take your work breakdown structure information

38
00:01:43,390 --> 00:01:47,450
and planned schedule, and then develop a base line plan.

39
00:01:47,450 --> 00:01:49,360
Simply put, this is a plan that defines

40
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:52,290
what the project manager hopes the project will look like.

41
00:01:52,290 --> 00:01:54,550
It includes cost, time and goal factors

42
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:56,460
using reasonable estimates.

43
00:01:56,460 --> 00:01:57,990
The base line plan provides guidance

44
00:01:57,990 --> 00:02:00,160
in all stages of the project.

45
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:03,420
Some call it a road map to our project success.

46
00:02:03,420 --> 00:02:05,050
As information is collected it can then

47
00:02:05,050 --> 00:02:07,560
be compared with this base line plan.

48
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:10,430
Because plans seldom eventuate as expected,

49
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:12,760
it becomes important to understand and investigate

50
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:15,160
any differences from the plan, and then decide

51
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:17,370
if any action is necessary.

52
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:19,190
The timing of this work is important

53
00:02:19,190 --> 00:02:20,800
as there needs to be sufficient time

54
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:23,670
to allow for early detection of any inconsistencies

55
00:02:23,670 --> 00:02:26,010
and correction of any causes.

56
00:02:26,010 --> 00:02:29,210
If differences from the base line plan are significant,

57
00:02:29,210 --> 00:02:31,240
correction action would be required in order

58
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,770
to bring the project back in line

59
00:02:32,770 --> 00:02:35,790
with the original or revised plan.

60
00:02:35,790 --> 00:02:38,170
In some cases, project scope may have

61
00:02:38,170 --> 00:02:42,210
changed, which will result in a change in the base line plan.

62
00:02:42,210 --> 00:02:44,085
Measuring and reporting progress is important

63
00:02:44,085 --> 00:02:46,360
but requires you, the project manager,

64
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:49,390
to think through what it is you are going to measure,

65
00:02:49,390 --> 00:02:52,020
the information required, and your ability

66
00:02:52,020 --> 00:02:54,460
to access that information.

